The paper deals with learning probabilistic models, specifically Markov networks and dependency networks. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The methods presented involve optimization and statistical inference, which are also relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses consistency and approximation, which are topics in statistical inference (cs.SI) and information theory (cs.IT).
